The paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to monitor and analyze aircraft noise in communities surrounding airports. This falls under the broad category of signal processing and analysis, which is covered by cs.SD (Signal Processing), making it the most likely sub-category. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for this task also suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.SI (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques such as CNNs suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
